==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decollation
<hw>De`col*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>decollatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧collation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of beheading or state of one beheaded; --
especially used of the execution of St. John the Baptist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A painting representing the beheading of a saint or
martyr, esp. of St. John the Baptist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decolletage</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
